{
  "esm": "0.6.0",
  "metadata": {
    "name": "area_eff_edge_faq",
    "description": "M3 cross-binding conformance fixture (RFC semiring-faq-unified-ir §7.3 / §7.1; bead ess-my4.3.10): the DOWNSTREAM geometric FAQ of the §7.3 mesh-edge worked example — the second half of the value-invention end-to-end chain. The first half (mesh-edge enumeration: a bool_and_or + distinct aggregate over faces, filter a<b, key skolem(edge,a,b), then a rank densify) MINTS the deduplicated `edges` index set; that half is a CONST-fold (build-time relational engine) whose byte-identical output is pinned by the determinism `edge_enumeration` golden and the cadence `pure_topology` golden across Julia/Rust/Python. Post-fold, `edges` is a PRIMITIVE index set, and this fixture is the geometric FAQ that consumes it: a default sum_product contraction over `edges`, the operation that replaces imperative per-edge Julia. The mesh is the same canonical 2-triangle mesh (faces {1,2,3},{2,3,4}) whose 5 unique undirected edges [[1,2],[1,3],[2,3],[2,4],[3,4]] rank to dense ids 0..4 — so `edges` is declared here as the materialized interval of size 5. State area_eff[i] accumulates the sum-of-products geometric contraction Sum_{e in edges} i*e: the per-edge geometric weight (the MPAS DUO term 1/4*dc*dv) is modeled by the edge index e and the per-cell factor by i, so the fixture stays inline-data-free and evaluates byte-for-byte identically across the three numeric bindings — the same index-arithmetic discipline as fvm_diffusion_sum_product (§7.1) and join_moves_running_exhaust (§7.2). area_eff[1]=Sum_{e=1..5}1*e=15, area_eff[2]=Sum_{e=1..5}2*e=30 at t=1 from zero initial conditions (constant-RHS shape, so Julia/Rust/Python agree to integration tolerance). The contracted index e is drawn from the `edges` interval index set via {from} (§5.2); the output index i uses a dense range so every binding sizes the state array identically. Together with the value-invention half (skolem_distinct_rank / pure_topology, verified byte-identically) this completes the §7.3 chain end to end: enumerate -> dedup/skolem -> rank -> consume `edges` as a primitive index set in an ordinary sum_product FAQ.",
    "authors": [
      "EarthSciSerialization/polecats/gastown.nux"
    ],
    "tags": [
      "aggregate",
      "semiring",
      "sum_product",
      "index-set",
      "value-invention",
      "edge-enumeration",
      "geometric-faq",
      "conformance",
      "ess-my4.3.10"
    ]
  },
  "models": {
    "AreaEffEdgeFaq": {
      "tolerance": {
        "rel": 1e-6,
        "abs": 1e-9
      },
      "index_sets": {
        "edges": {
          "kind": "interval",
          "size": 5
        }
      },
      "variables": {
        "area_eff": { "type": "state", "shape": ["i"] }
      },
      "equations": [
        {
          "_comment": "D(area_eff[i])/dt = sum_{e in edges} i*e (default sum_product). `edges` is the materialized §7.3 edge set (the 5 unique undirected edges of the 2-triangle mesh, ranked to dense ids 0..4), consumed here as a PRIMITIVE index set. Sum_{e=1..5} e = 15, so area_eff[i]=15i: [1]=15, [2]=30 at t=1.",
          "lhs": {
            "op": "aggregate",
            "args": [],
            "output_idx": ["i"],
            "expr": {
              "op": "D",
              "args": [{ "op": "index", "args": ["area_eff", "i"] }],
              "wrt": "t"
            },
            "ranges": { "i": [1, 2] }
          },
          "rhs": {
            "op": "aggregate",
            "args": [],
            "output_idx": ["i"],
            "semiring": "sum_product",
            "ranges": { "i": [1, 2], "e": { "from": "edges" } },
            "expr": { "op": "*", "args": ["i", "e"] }
          }
        }
      ],
      "tests": [
        {
          "id": "area_eff_edge_faq_t1",
          "description": "Constant-RHS sum_product geometric FAQ over the materialized `edges` primitive index set (size 5) from zero ICs. area_eff[i]=15i at t=1 (Sum_{e=1..5} e = 15).",
          "initial_conditions": {
            "area_eff[1]": 0.0,
            "area_eff[2]": 0.0
          },
          "time_span": { "start": 0.0, "end": 1.0 },
          "assertions": [
            { "variable": "area_eff[1]", "time": 1.0, "expected": 15.0 },
            { "variable": "area_eff[2]", "time": 1.0, "expected": 30.0 }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  }
}
